{"change_summary":"Removed the unsafe default implementations for milestone journal/task-run atomic helpers, added a milestone-scoped writer lock in the filesystem snapshot adapter, and routed status, plan, bead-start, and task-run completion mutations through that lock so snapshot, lineage, and journal updates serialize correctly. `record_bead_start` now rejects terminal milestones before mutating lineage, and new regressions cover terminal-start rejection plus concurrent completion/start serialization.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage."],"steps":[{"description":"Made milestone mutation atomicity explicit in the service traits by removing the non-locking default implementations for `append_event_if_missing` and `record_task_run_start`, and by requiring snapshot stores to provide a milestone-scoped write lock.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Implemented the filesystem-backed milestone mutation lock and updated `update_status`, `persist_plan`, `record_bead_start`, and `update_task_run` to run their snapshot/lineage/journal writes under that shared lock, including a pre-write terminal-milestone rejection in `record_bead_start`.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Added regression coverage for rejecting starts on completed milestones without stray lineage writes and for serializing a completion against a concurrent new start so snapshot state cannot be overwritten by stale writes.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 77 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}